trait-basic-Breasts-name = Basic breasts
trait-basic-Breasts-desc = You have a pair of mammarian glands, producing up to 30 units of milk every 10 minutes.

trait-basic-Penis-name = Basic penis
trait-basic-Penis-desc = You have an appendage producing up to 15 units of semen every 10 minutes.

trait-basic-Vagina-name = Basic vagina
trait-basic-Vagina-desc = You have a reproductive system producing up to 10 units of lubricant and leaving at least 20 units of space for deposition.

trait-basic-Rectum-name = Basic rectum
trait-basic-Rectum-desc = Your anal tunnel is accessible for deposition of up to 30 units of fluids. Doesn't produce anything.


# Bonuses
trait-double-production-name = Double fluid production
trait-double-production-desc = All lewd organs you choose produce fluids twice as fast as specified in the description.

trait-quadruple-production-name = Quadruple fluid production
trait-quadruple-production-desc = All lewd organs you choose produce fluids four times as fast as specified in the description.

# Factorio flashbacks...
trait-double-production-capacity-name = Double production capacity
trait-double-capacity-desc = All lewd organs you choose can produce twice as much liquids before stopping.

trait-quadruple-production-capacity-name = Quadruple production capacity
trait-quadruple-capacity-desc = All lewd organs you choose can produce four times as much liquids before stopping.

trait-deposition-capacity-20-name = Double storage capacity
trait-deposition-capacity-20-desc = All organs allowing deposition (currently vagina and rectum) can store 20 more units of fluids. They will still drain.

trait-deposition-capacity-40-name = Quadruple storage capacity
trait-deposition-capacity-40-desc = All organs allowing deposition (currently vagina and rectum) can store 40 more units of fluids. They will still drain.

trait-void-deposit-name = Void organs
trait-void-deposit-desc = You must have a black hole inside your lewd organs, for any fluids that go inside shrimply vanish over time, without leaking outside.
